</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-124_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-125_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-126_ pf-heading-1-h3">Strategies for teaching teams</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-128_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Teaching teams how to work effectively together is critical in health and social care, where teamwork is essential. Team teaching involves a unique set of dynamics, where clear communication, flexibility, and the management of power dynamics are key.<br><br>Reflecting on team performance through post-session debriefs and peer evaluations can help identify areas for improvement and reinforce successful strategies. By fostering a collaborative environment, educators can ensure that their teaching teams are cohesive, effective, and aligned with the overall goals of the training program.<br>
